prompt: Heatmap of traffic volume between top 10 port pairs
code:
import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
sql_query = """
SELECT 
    "input port", 
    "output port", 
    SUM(packet_size) AS total_traffic
FROM 
    table_8b203ce1c2a958757008b6ae93d9f30d
GROUP BY 
    "input port", "output port"
ORDER BY 
    total_traffic DESC
LIMIT 10
"""
top_port_pairs = execute_sql_query(sql_query)
heatmap_data = top_port_pairs.pivot(index='input port', columns='output port', values='total_traffic').fillna(0)
plt.figure(figsize=(10, 8))
sns.heatmap(heatmap_data, annot=True, fmt='.0f', cmap='YlGnBu')
plt.title('Heatmap of Traffic Volume Between Top 10 Port Pairs')
plt.xlabel('Output Port')
plt.ylabel('Input Port')
plt.savefig('exports/charts/temp_chart_be3f0d29-f3cf-4e8b-a929-2414066aa7aa.png')
plt.close()
result = {'type': 'plot', 'value': 'exports/charts/temp_chart_be3f0d29-f3cf-4e8b-a929-2414066aa7aa.png'}
